# what2play-services — repo context

This repo is the **application API layer** in the What 2 Play split: API Gateway, Node Lambdas, app DynamoDB, and Terraform for this stack only. Shared infra (Cognito, static hosting, DNS, post-confirmation Lambda) lives in **what2play-infrastructure**; the web app is **what2play-client**. See `README.md` breadcrumbs.

## Security posture (solo portfolio)

Prefer **service-level wildcard IAM actions with tightly scoped `Resource` ARNs** over grinding least-privilege lists. OIDC trust should stay as narrow as you are willing (branch/repo). Document intentional tradeoffs in Terraform comments when non-obvious.

## README and terraform-docs

Keep human-written sections **above** `<!-- BEGIN_TF_DOCS -->`. Do not edit the fenced terraform-docs block by hand; regenerate with your terraform-docs workflow when the module changes.

## Lambda error contract

API Lambdas often use `throw JSON.stringify({ statusCode, error: message })`. In Jest, assert with `await expect(handler(...)).rejects.toBe(JSON.stringify({ ... }))`, not `rejects.toThrow()`.

